headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey had 28 points and 12 rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons overcame Norman Powell's 43 points to beat the Toronto Raptors 116-112 on Wednesday night, ending a four-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey's double-double leads Pistons over slumping Raptors

headlines.description: — James Harden had 40 points, 15 assists and 10 rebounds for his 11th triple-double of the season, leading the Brooklyn Nets to a 124-115 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden has triple-double, short-handed Nets top Pacers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 10 of his 32 points in overtime to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 109-105 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night in a matchup of two of the Eastern Conference’s best teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo lifts Bucks to 109-105 OT victory over 76ers

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 28 points and hit a jumper over Bradley Beal with 0.7 seconds remaining to give the Sacramento Kings a 121-119 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox hits game-winner over Beal, Kings beat Wizards 121-119

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 29 points, Darius Garland added 25 and Cleveland's young guards made big plays down the stretch as the Cavaliers ended a four-game losing streak with a 117-110 win over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton, Garland help Cavs snap 4-game slide, beat Celtics

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl tied a career high with 20 points and set one with 16 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs used a huge fourth quarter to beat the Chicago Bulls 106-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl has 20 points, 16 rebounds as Spurs rally past Bulls

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Draymond Green had 16 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists and the Golden State Warriors handed the Houston Rockets their franchise-record 18th straight loss, 108-94 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors hand Rockets franchise-record 18th straight loss

headlines.description: — Ja Morant dribbled the length of the court for a tiebreaking layup with 1.2 seconds left and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Miami Heat 89-85 on Wednesday night to end a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant layup with 1.2 seconds left lifts Grizzlies over Heat

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 12 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for another triple-double, Michael Porter Jr. added 28 points and the Denver Nuggets pulled away in the second half to beat the Charlotte Hornets 129-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has triple double, Nuggets beat Hornets 129-104

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 42 points and the Dallas Mavericks earned a split of a two-game set against their first-round playoff opponent from last season, beating the Los Angeles Clippers 105-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs answer, earn split with Clippers in 105-89 win
